title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog.
description: Currently, the output parameter is not being displayed in the data set dialog.
OB: The output parameter is not visible in the data set dialog when calling a stored procedure from Oracle database and storing the query result in the output parameter as an object.
EB: The output parameter should be visible in the data set dialog when calling a stored procedure from Oracle database and storing the query result in the output parameter as an object.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Call a stored procedure from Oracle database.
2. Store the query result in the output parameter as an object.
3. Open the data set dialog.
4. Verify if the output parameter is visible in the dialog.
